                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Prop for NHB, Exim
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Subbarao in Calcutta on Thursday. (PTI)                                  
	Calcutta, Dec. 11: The Reserve Bank of India today approved a Rs 4,000-crore line of credit for the National Housing Bank (NHB) and a Rs 9,000-crore refinancing facility for the Export Import Bank of India.        
	The RBI board met here today to take stock of the current economic conditions and the impact of its recent monetary measures.        
	Earlier, the apex bank had announced a slew of measures to stimulate the housing and export sectors, hit hard by the financial meltdown.        
	RBI governor D. Subbarao said, The central board has decided to lend more support to the housing and the export sectors, which had been adversely affected by the recent developments in the financial markets.        
	On Saturday, the RBI slashed a key lending rate by one percentage point to 6.5 per cent.         
	Subbarao said future policies would take into consideration the falling inflation rate.        
	He said the near-term outlook for the economy remained uncertain.                                                                                                                                      
